<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Pet level spells should work like PC spells of that level.  I actually think that if my earth pet's root spell worked like a level 40 player's root, I might actually be able to finish off a mob.<P>Expedience is a joke.  "This will allow a pet to 'keep up' with a fleeing mob."  Does Verant know that we have spells that do direct damage at a distance?  Or maybe if root or stun worked more than 1 out of 15 times.  I would much rather have a pet SoW for travelling through a dangerous zone (since our invisibility is a joke after level 30), that way my pet could <I>maybe</I> take a mob and get back to us.<P>Speaking of our pets, it certainly would have been nice of Verant to continue the Renew line of spells.  They seem to continue every other line at certain intervals, even with other classes...since we cannot heal group members unless we summon bandages(don't EVEN get me started on that one).  If our pets are supposed to be gaining experience, wouldn't it make sense to try to keep them around longer?  Chain casting is a "cheat".  I always thought that we were to care about our pet, after all, it is an extension of our will...<P>Summon companion is the best spell I have seen to make up for the tracking problems with pets in dungeons.  I would like to suggest a change, however.  I will usually set my pet to guard a spot or sit down.  It would be really nice if on summoning, the pet automatically resets to following me, since I am summoning him.<P>Just my 2cp...
</FONT>
