You may want to care for your pet...but me...my pet is simply an extension of my power summoned to do my bidding and be sent back to where they came from at my command.  You can shun chain casting..but I will not and neither will any other self respecting mage.  It is THE best way to efficiently handle mobs and it is VERY mage like.  I think its one of the most impressive displays of magician power and ingenuity to watch a good chain caster work (or BE a good chain caster at work)<P>If you want to roll play and not "kill" your pet, just ask yourself this, does it ever say that your are ending your pets life when you type /pet get lost..no he simply responds "As you wish Master.." or something like that.  Role play it like this...your pet is almost dead so instead of letting him die you send him back to his elements to recover for another day while at the same time calling more elemental power forth to continue your bidding.  <P>Chain casting is not a "cheat", you're just plain wrong.  <P>/steps down from soap box<P>--------------------<P>Tomlyn Drayke-Lvl 55 Conjurer<BR>Fallken Stallken-Lvl 25 Rogue<BR>Prexus<P>"He knows the guy with the bandages around his ass ain't goin nowhere.  He's goin f#%king nowhere. Where you goin...nowhere!" ---"Boondock Saints"
