<FONT SIZE="1" color="#000000" face="Verdana, Arial">
posted April 06, 2001 11:53 AM &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=edit_post&f=26&t=000040&reply_num=000004&u="><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/edit_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete Post"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=reply&f=26&t=000040&replyto=000004"><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/quote_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Reply With Quote"></A>
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Ok....maybe I overstated on chain-casting pets.<P>I think that chain-casting is more of a "manipulation" of the game, a way to "work around" some of the "deficiencies" of being a mage.  I have chained pets, and do it with no problem, however, I believe that there should be a different option...<P>I mean, c'mon...all other classes get upgrades to their heal spells, why shouldn't we?  When I'm in a group, I feel the need to be responsible to myself first, my pet second and the group third.  The reason I put the group third is that the group would normally be the clerics first priority (as well as the puller).  I feel like I have an obligation to heal my pet, to keep him in the game.<P>Renew Summoning is a joke after level 30.  Renew Summoning:  Increase Hit Points (HP) from 140 (L20) to 220 (L60). That means that you get a whopping 2 points of heal per level up to level 60. How many hits from a giant in Frontier Mountains does it take to go through 160 HP's at level 30? I'll tell you.  Exactly 3.<P>Let's do some math.  It takes 3.5 ticks for a cast time and 2.5 ticks for recovery.  A total of 5 ticks combined.  In 5 ticks can a giant hit your pet 3 times?  You betcha... How many times? Probably about 6.  So in the time it takes for you to replenish 160 pet HP's you've lost 320.  Not very mana efficient.  Your pet will be dead in a matter of seconds if you don't cast a nuke.<P>All I am really trying to get at is, if we can't heal ourselves or others, at least give us the means to heal our pets.  At least more than we can now...<P>Our pets are already outclassed by the mobs, (they hit for about 1/2 - 2/3 of what a similar mob hits for and have far fewer HP) which is why they need us.  Why cant we be the cleric to our tanks?  Why should we have to summon a new warrior?  I just think there should be options...
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
