You wanna know why I think they stopped that line...because they're smart.  Look at your last healing spell and the mana it uses 100 mana I believe.  Now look at all the pets after level 20.  (ok except for 24 which is weird 240 mana cost.)  All pets until level 51 pet costs 200 mana.  Any upgrade to our heal spell would cost 200 mana or more and wouldn't be a complete heal.  If we ever did get a complete pet heal, it would be well into the 50's and would cost ALOT of mana.  If you're soloing, the cost of casting that over a new pet would probably have some efficiency questions.  If you're grouping and your pet needs a heal, you get a healer in your group to do it.  I had alot more rant after this but deleted it.  Was more rambling.  Enjoy your mage and learn to chain cast for goodness sake.  You'll avoid alot of headaches.<P>--------------------<P>Tomlyn Drayke-Lvl 55 Conjurer<BR>Fallken Stallken-Lvl 25 Rogue<BR>Prexus<P>"He knows the guy with the bandages around his ass ain't goin nowhere.  He's goin f#%king nowhere. Where you goin...nowhere!" ---"Boondock Saints"
