<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Hail, fello mages,<P>I can understand all of you. But I cant agree with all of you.<P>You want a better heal for our pets? Yes, would be nice, but it is not really needed in my opinion. I still use my renew spell at lvl 42. I just made a few tries on Gornit - and tactic here was nuke, heal, nuke, heal till Gornit is dead. And it works - makes it challenging to defeat that mob. I always have the feeling some of us just want to lvl quickly to be that uber-mage.<P>Remember EQ is about grouping, teaming, fighting together. Therefore not all classes can do everything. You want a healed pet, well grab a cleric or even better a druid or shaman. you want a maximum buffed pet and hate long downtimes, grab an enchanter and so on and so on ... be creative ... start grouping ... its not hard to find someONE who will group with us.<P>The fact mages are not wanted: Not true, you just have to see it from the opposite perspective. I never got a tell: "Oh you are a mage, ahh not sorry we dont want you in our group". NEVER. Especially not after I grouped with them before and they saw what me and Jabober can do. We are powerfull !!! Get to 39th and see what a fire pet can do to a mob if you have at least one more tank (not hard to find).<P>In fact I dare to say: You have two or three mages in group, what the hell do you want with a tank or cleric. We dont even need them. I fight constantly in a group with two mages and two chanters. to be honest we rock and have very small downtime and I can pull nearly as fast a tank cleric group. Try it if you dont believe me.<P>Once had a four mages group + chanter. We didnt even used nukes but chatted the whole time. When one pet died, we just summoned a new one. Easy like this.<P>But what we really could use is some new summon weapon stuff - thats waht we are for. We are summoners - we dont really need mundane stuff - we are pure arcane magic ...<P>And now group, have fun with your mage - or quit playing him. The less mages there are the more special the remaining ones are ... muhahaha ... once they will fear most unnoticed class in everquest ... as a phoenix out of the ashes. I ll stick to my mage. Because I have fun in roleplaying AND playing him.<P>Greets to you all.<P>Melvyn Ghostwalker<BR>42nd circle of knowledge<BR>humble mage on Bristlebain<P>P.S.: I like summon companion and expedience. I like our nukes also ;-) But most I like my pet.
