<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I would not like summon pet spell to change, i can always tell pet to folow me right after i summon him. I have use pet summon to help me alot in unfamiliar outdoor zones. I would park pet where i zoned in at or somewhere safe and explore *namely oot lately* and would get totally lost hehe so i would summon my pet and watch him lead me back to safety    <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> yea sure its not much but hey why change that nice lil feature just because u dont like to push your /pet guard here hot key.<BR>about the renew summon spell vs chain casting pets issue. IMHO I think its a wonderfull spell even at 52 yes i think it needs a serious upgrade but I still mem the spell and use it greatly vs apropiate mobs. like for instance low blues seafuries and DL creatures and even ganshers in skyfire, I can heal pet 3 to 4 times during fight and be ready for next kill when its done. But now if you are fighting something that out classes your pet seriously like for instance a mature wurm or a named seafurie, then yea renew suxors you best be summoning your next pet and have /pet get lost at your finger tips. I believe renew summons definately needs an upgrade but to say it useless after 30 is not by anymeans using all your abilities in the right circumstances. also as a note it also depends what pet you choose to hunt with for instance at 52 I use my monster pet lvl 50 still *summons til fire* yea hes lower level than my earth 51 but he takes alot less dmg per hit and returns alot with its DS so with this sort of pet and low blues I just heal 2 or three time and its no contest. but with say a 51 earth and same mob he gets hit more takes more dmg thus you could prolly save a good deal of mana by just summoning a new pet cause by time it heals up or u heal it up 3 times the sitting will take place. and thats including rebuffs on new pet.<BR>All depends on how ya wanna play and even though some think we are just pet nuke we do have alot of avenues of getting the job done and a smart magician will look at all different situations and decide which is best to make him/herself and/or group more efficient.<BR>Only true rant i have atm is the damn Coh nerf which i was looking so foward to getting  <IMG SRC="frown.gif" border="0"><BR>Thank you for hearing my thoughts.<BR>Keare Elementalweaver<BR>52 elementalist
